headline: Prediction: This Artificial Intelligence (AI) Semiconductor Stock Is Set to Soar After Dec. 18
summary: Shares of the memory specialist are down 27% since hitting a 52-week high in mid-June.  Micron Technology is known for manufacturing memory chips for both computing and storage.  This explains why the global memory market plunged nearly 39% last year, as per Gartner's estimates, owing to a 4.4% drop in shipments of PCs, smartphones, and tablets.
